Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). In a large bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter. Pat into bottom of a 9x13 inch pan. Bake at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). For 10 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to cool. In a sauce pan, mix pudding with milk and cook according to package directions. It will be very stiff. In a large bowl, mix pudding and cream cheese together until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spread over cooled graham cracker crust. Top with fruit filling. Refrigerate until served.